We must find the gross profit from sales by taking each “Sale” transaction and summing its “profit” field. (That “profit” is already provided on the sale record as the difference between the sale‘after‐tax amount’ and its “cost_amount”.)

Below we extract each “Sale” record from the dataset and note the profit value:

1. For id Sale20240103002 – profit = 302111.59

15. For id Sale20240205041 – profit = 428329.11  

Now we sum these values step‐by‐step:

• 302111.59 + 460946.33 = 763057.92  
• 763057.92 + 489365.79 = 1252423.71  
• 1252423.71 + 174738.01 = 1427161.72  
• 1427161.72 + 151423.21 = 1578584.93  
• 1578584.93 + 324652.91 = 1903237.84  
• 1903237.84 + 366055.78 = 2269293.62  
• 2269293.62 + 350635.95 = 2619929.57  
• 2619929.57 + 159057.20 = 2778986.77  
• 2778986.77 + 499323.77 = 3278310.54  
• 3278310.54 + 210732.40 = 3489042.94  
• 3489042.94 + 384532.44 = 3873575.38  
• 3873575.38 + 563873.27 = 4437448.65  
• 4437448.65 + 502579.13 = 4940027.78  
• 4940027.78 + 428329.11 = 5368356.89  

Thus the sum of the profits from all sales is 5,368,356.89. This figure is our final gross profit for the income statement.
